1 I was told that they couldn't wash your car with snow on it and that I was supposed to get rid of all the ice before bringing it there. 10 bucks and still had snow on my back bumper. The owner then told me it was my truck, not his wash. After a long lecture I did get a new wash. You're better off getting gas station car wash.
5 He did not have any snow on the back of  his vehicle. He had a mound of frozen kitty litter on the back of his bumper that he said his parents had spilled. We were happy to rewash him and will treat every customers vehicle like our own.
